      <h1 class="heading-xlarge">Find a traineeship</h1>

      <div class="text">
        <p>You can apply for a traineeship if you’re:</p>

        <ul class="list-bullet">
          <li>eligible to work in England</li>
          <li>unemployed and have little or no work experience</li>
          <li>aged 16 to 18 and qualified below Level 3, or aged 19 to 24 and qualified below Level 2</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="panel-indent">You may be ready for an <a href="/apprentice/search-index.html">apprenticeship</a> if you already have some work experience.</div>

        <div class="get-started form-group">
        <a href="search-index.html" class="button">Start now</a>
          <!-- <span class="destination">on apprenticeship vacancy matching service</span> -->
        </div>

        <h2 class="heading-medium">Before you start</h2>

        <p>A traineeship is a course to get you ready for work or an apprenticeship. It can take up to 6 months.</p>

        <p>You’ll get:</p>

        <ul class="list-bullet">
          <li>help with English and maths (if you need it)</li>
          <li>a work experience placement lasting at least 6 weeks</li>
        </ul>

        <p>You won’t be paid, but your employers can sometimes give you expenses for things like travel and meals.</p>

        <h2 class="heading-medium">Get advice</h2>

        <p>Contact the <a href="https://nationalcareersservice.direct.gov.uk/Pages/Home.aspx" rel="external">National Careers Service</a> for advice.</p>
